People Tree,Ethical Fashion,"Outstanding clothing for people with Autistm, sensory and/or allergy sensitivities","I have received two orders over the past 2 months from People Tree. The garments are wonderful! I have Asperger's and people on the spectrum can have great difficulty with clothing because of our sensory sensitivities. Anything from clothing tags, seams, fabric texture, fit, reactions to synthetic materials can all create a high level of discomfort akin to having severe dry itchy skin or a sunburn (strange, I know). People Tree is the first company where I can wear anything and nothing hurts. The garments I've purchased are organic cotton (regular, brushed, and flannel) and Tencel. I look forward to trying their Linen garments as I'm a big fan of flax as an eco-friendly crop. I originally wanted to buy from PT because they stand for ethical slow fashion, human rights, and environmental protection. They care.  But being able to wear clothing that doesn't hurt me is an incredible experience. Thank-you PT for (unintentionally?!) making Autistic friendly garments. On to the shipping experience (amid a pandemic): The first order saw some complications regarding delayed shipping and unanswered emails which led to a lot of frustration and irate emails on my end however it got resolved and as a gesture of goodwill, PT refunded the shipping fee (shipping outside UK).  The second order saw an older item (reiko trousers) out of stock in my size and the shipment didn't go out 'right away' because the CSR wanted to make absolute certain that the trousers were, in fact, out of stock. I appreciated that. It was confirmed they were out of stock and a refund was processed same day.  Highly recommend PT.  They have some hiccups, for sure, but they're human beings open to constructive feedback and, well, Rome wasn't built in a day.",5,2021-04-12 11:18:32+00:00,Trustpilot
